# Alpha Identity Grouping (RTL)

The problem is **identity grouping**, not text alignment.

## Identity block (one attached group, starts from the right)

**Avatar + Name + Shield + Role** must live in a single `.alpha-identity-block`.

- Avatar must **never** be a separate flex sibling away from name/shield
- Role / rank / presence label belongs **inside** the identity block (`meta` prop)
- Use `AlphaIdentityRow` — do not hand-build rows

## Outside the identity block

- **`subtitle`** — non-identity content (message preview)
- **`trailing`** — actions, counters, controls, time, badges, chevrons

Identity information must **never** split across the row.

## Structure

```
.alpha-identity-row
  .alpha-identity-block          ← attached unit (RTL, from the right)
    .alpha-identity-block__avatar
    .alpha-identity-block__details
      .alpha-identity-name      ← name + shield
      .alpha-identity-block__role
  .alpha-identity-row__secondary  ← optional preview
  .alpha-identity-row__trailing    ← controls only
```

## Forbidden

- `[avatar] [body column]` as top-level row siblings without `.alpha-identity-block` wrapper
- Putting role/presence in `trailing` or `subtitle`
- Per-screen `dir`, `justify-end`, or alignment props on identity pieces
